problem: Define the operation $\star$ by $a \star b = (a + b)b$. What is $(3\star5) - (5\star3)$?
model_solution:
Step 1: Calculate $3 \star 5$.
$3 \star 5 = (3 + 5)5$
$= (8)5$
Step 2: Calculate $3 \star 5$.
$3 \star 5 = 8 \cdot 5$
$= 40$

Step 3: Calculate $5 \star 3$.
$5 \star 3 = (5 + 3)3$
$= (8)3$
$= 24$

Step 4: Find $(3\star5) - (5\star3)$.
$(3\star5) - (5\star3) = 40 - 24$
$= 16$
